what to type in command prompt to execute a .c file to .o file :

i) gcc -o <file_name_after_compilation> <file1.c> <file2.c> <file3.c>.......

eg -> gcc -o CompiledProgram main.c functions.c

ii) also we need to create a header file that already contains the definition
    of the methods used in functions file beforehand to avoid compilation errors.

for more info, read : https://chat.openai.com/share/30e7eed3-39d3-4ebb-8a60-c788d38b65ad

we can also use 'clang' compiler instead of 'gcc' in above like shown below
eg -> clang -o CompiledProgram main.c functions.c
